<br>
Yes, we do ALL loot in POH/POF random by elimination.  There are no dibs on any loot for RR's or for guests, including epic drops.  We believe that's the right way to do it.  We readily invite anyone to join us.  And we think doing it with such a mix of folks makes it all the more challenging and FUN.  Our guests are just as important a part of making the raid work as we are. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We would hope all guilds might do it this way, but we are only one guild.<br>
<br>
As for the continuing debate, I lean towards making several days a week FFA, and yes NOT FIF.  I think that patch day should be one of those days.  And I'd like to see how that works.  I hear the &quot;we should go in anytime we want&quot; and wonder how this matches with &quot;we don't need any of the planar armors&quot;.  I don't think big necessarily means BAD, and I never blame a whole guild for the actions of a few.  Oddly, I hope a new Summit could serve the needs of both sides of this debate, but I rarely see compromise in most of the rhetoric.  And that's sad.<br>
