<br>
It's not compromising everyone to use a system that a lot of those people don't want.  A lot of us want a scheduled system.  And it's strictly due to the amount of effort that goes into assembling the forces required.  If I could pull together the forces on short notice, I wouldn't care so much.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, envision this...  We gather at G'fay wizzie spires.  We've purchased a bunch of Hate port stones.  Now we're going to port up, but we don't know if anyone is there.  I don't know of a way to do a &quot;who all hatezone&quot;, so we have to send at least one group up there to see.  But if it's just one group, they could easily get wiped out, so I have to send three groups at least.<br>
<br>
Three port stones just to find out IF the plane is taken.<br>
<br>
Plus I've invested the cash for enough stones for the entire raid.  If we don't use them, that ties up what is for us a lot of cash.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, there's another issue.  It's a lot lot easier for a guild to move its own forces around Norrath.  But trying to move a multi-guild raid around is a bit harder.  People go LD and don't have /guildsay to catch up.  Lots of other issues.<br>
<br>
And how many times would I assemble the forces together, just to find that the place we really wanted to go was already taken?  Probably 19 out of 20 times.  Given that I'm not going to try this every single night, no, I am NOT going to get to the planes more often than I do.<br>
<br>
Guilds like TD will, because it's a lot easier for them to assemble forces.  And the funds aren't the same issue for you, either.  Just make a walk-through of juggs in seb, collect some spells, maybe whack the king and get a fungi, and you're set on raid funds for weeks.  I don't have those kinds of resources.<br>
<br>
The guilds that want complete FFA are the ones who can assemble the forces required on relatively short notice.  Furthermore, their requirements are a lot smaller because average level is close to 60, average gear is a heck of a lot better.  I suspect guilds like TD can break Fear with 2 groups.  I can do it with 3, but it's my best 3, and sometimes we have to evac once or twice after killing a few mobs.<br>
<br>
So the compromise a lot of us want is part scheduled, part FFA or FiF.  The compromise from your end would be to at least give it an honest try and see how it works.<br>
<br>
We're even suggesting Tuesdays and Wednesdays -- the popular patch days, when mobs will be up.  It just seems to me that the number of guilds asking for FFA is small enough that 8 days a month in each plane should be able to handle their demands.<br>
<br>
And if not -- if a lot of other guilds are taking advantage of FFA days, then maybe we need to change how many each week.  But I would expect the summit would have language that prohibited guilds that have bookings from using FFA.  So I think there's room for some balance that's fair to everyone.<br>
<br>
<br>
